How-to use highlightening for ANSYS macro files (i.e. files in the APDL language or WorkBench Command (APDL) objects).

Get it at http://www.mecheng.adelaide.edu.au/~will/ansys/ansys-mod.el  
(The file at http://ansys.net/ansys/tools/ansys-mod.el is broken.)


* download ansys-mod.el to your elisp-file directory
* add the following to your .emacs file assuming your ansys files are named *.ans

    (autoload 'ansys-mode "ansys-mod" nil t)
    (add-to-list 'auto-mode-alist '("\\.ans\\'" . ansys-mode))


[new]]]
 For a more powerful and up to date Ansys mode, based on ANSYS v19 and written for Emacs 25 and later, please have a look at [[APDLMode]] -- [[dida]]
